summary: Novak Djokovic - Alexander Zverev (Head-to-Head) Novak will face Alexander Zverev in the final of the Nitto ATP Finals on Sunday...
caption:
Novak Djokovic - Alexander Zverev (Head-to-Head)

Novak will face Alexander Zverev in the final of the Nitto ATP Finals on Sunday not before 6 PM local time (not before 7 PM CET). 

They faced each other in the group stage where Novak won in straight sets.

Novak is looking for his fifth title this season, his sixth ATP World Tour Finals title and his 73rd career title.

(via atpworldtour.com)

summary: Ivan Rakitic: ‘We saw Football’s Coming Home and thought: yeah, but you still have to play us’
title: Ivan Rakitic: ‘We saw Football’s Coming Home and thought: yeah, but you still have to play us’
excerpt: The Barcelona and Croatia midfielder talks about playing England at the World Cup with a virus, how to stay calm when taking penalties and post-tournament exhaustion
description:
He insists he feels Swiss and a little Spanish, but is Croatian “to the final hair on my head”, and recalls a package arriving in Möhlin during the 1998 World Cup containing Croatia shirts for him and his brother. Now, his team had gone further. How did he feel, standing there pre-final, national anthem playing?

“That’s a great question,” he says. “You think …”

There is a long pause. Eventually, he says: “You feel a pride so strong that if Superman flew down, he couldn’t drag you away; he couldn’t shift you, so powerful is the desire, the will. It’s amazing. You experience emotions you’ll never forget. It’s unique. I’ve been fortunate to win the Champions League but, with respect, even that doesn’t come close. You think: ‘OK, stop everything, let’s play.’”

PALLAMANO FEMMINILE A2 / CINGOLI SI AGGIUDICA IL DERBY SUL CHIARAVALLE

Cingoli   –  Chiaravalle   37-18

CINGOLI, 18 novembre 2018 – Torna alla vittoria il Setterosa della Polisportiva Cingoli.

Le ragazze di Analla si sono aggiudicate per 37-28 il derby contro il Chiaravalle, valido per la quinta giornata di Serie A2 Femminile. Dopo un primo tempo equilibrato, le cingolane hanno sfruttato il calo delle avversarie e hanno messo in ghiaccio la sfida.
